### **Debian 2 â€” Nginx Reverse Proxy**

```bash
# IP: 192.168.80.130

sudo apt-get update && sudo apt-get install nginx -y

# Remove default config
sudo rm /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/*

# Create reverse proxy config
sudo nano /etc/nginx/sites-available/rp.conf
```

Add:

```nginx
server {
    listen 80;
    location / {
        proxy_pass http://192.168.80.129;
    }
}
```

```bash
# Link config to enabled sites
sudo ln -s /etc/nginx/sites-available/rp.conf /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/

# Test config
sudo nginx -t

# Restart nginx
sudo systemctl restart nginx
```

âœ… **Test:** Open browser â†’ [http://192.168.80.130](http://192.168.80.130) â†’ Should show **â€œHello Worldâ€**

